From 8b9f9c443be15f3b2ac334286b3f36cc1eda70a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Peter van der Perk <peter.vanderperk@nxp.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 12:28:22 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] i3c: hub: p3h2840: hold etx_mutex across SMBus transaction
 wait

read_smbus_transaction_status() dropped etx_mutex during the completion
sleep. The descriptor, TX data and readback all share the single
PAGE_PTR register, so the IBI handler or a concurrent agent-port transfer
could repaginate mid-transaction and corrupt the readback (seen as EDID
bit-flips and cross-port corruption).

Keep the lock held across the wait. Bonus: no extra PAGE_PTR re-write, so
less agent traffic and fewer spurious controller IBIs.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Peter van der Perk <peter.vanderperk@nxp.com>
---
 drivers/i3c/hub/p3h2840_i3c_hub_smbus.c | 10 ++++++++--
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i3c/hub/p3h2840_i3c_hub_smbus.c b/drivers/i3c/hub/p3h2840_i3c_hub_smbus.c
index 42d5673a3982..5a2d6e27098b 100644
--- a/drivers/i3c/hub/p3h2840_i3c_hub_smbus.c
+++ b/drivers/i3c/hub/p3h2840_i3c_hub_smbus.c
@@ -150,9 +150,12 @@ static int p3h2x4x_read_smbus_transaction_status(struct p3h2x4x_i3c_hub_dev *hub
 	u8 status;
 	int ret;
 
-	mutex_unlock(&hub->etx_mutex);
+	/*
+	 * Hold etx_mutex across the wait. Descriptor/TX/readback all share
+	 * PAGE_PTR; dropping it here lets the IBI handler or another agent
+	 * port repaginate and corrupt the readback.
+	 */
 	fsleep(P3H2X4X_SMBUS_400KHZ_TRANSFER_TIMEOUT(data_length));
-	mutex_lock(&hub->etx_mutex);
 
 	ret = regmap_read(hub->regmap, target_port_status, &status_read);
 	if (ret)
